Fix: Deneb gateway facts parsing failure (importance.go)
=========================================================

Target: choiceoh/Deneb — gateway-go/internal/memory/importance.go

Root Cause
----------
importanceMaxTokens = 512 is too low for Korean content with Qwen3.5 thinking tags.

When the LLM response exceeds 512 tokens, the JSON output gets truncated mid-stream,
producing invalid JSON like:

  {"facts": [{"content": "사용자가...", "category": "context", "importance": 0.6,
  "expiry_hint": null}, {"content": "터미널 로그 확

All 5 parsing cases in parseFactsResponse fail on truncated JSON, causing the
"could not parse facts from response" debug log.

Token budget breakdown (worst case):
  - <think>...</think> tags from Qwen3.5: ~100-200 tokens
  - JSON structure overhead: ~50 tokens
  - 7 Korean facts × ~40-60 tokens each: ~280-420 tokens
  - Total: ~430-670 tokens → exceeds 512

Fix (2 changes)
---------------

1. Increase importanceMaxTokens: 512 → 1536

   const (
       importanceTimeout   = 30 * time.Second
   -   importanceMaxTokens = 512
   +   importanceMaxTokens = 1536
   )

2. Add truncated JSON recovery as Case 6 fallback in parseFactsResponse.
   Even with more tokens, edge cases can still truncate. This recovers
   whatever complete facts exist in a truncated response.

   Add at the end of parseFactsResponse, before "return nil, false":

   // Case 6: truncated JSON recovery — close unclosed brackets and retry.
   if recovered, ok := tryRecoverTruncatedJSON(text); ok {
       return recovered, true
   }

   New helper function:

   // tryRecoverTruncatedJSON attempts to recover facts from truncated JSON.
   // When max_tokens cuts the response mid-JSON, extract whatever complete
   // fact objects exist by finding the last complete "}" boundary.
   func tryRecoverTruncatedJSON(text string) ([]ExtractedFact, bool) {
       idx := strings.Index(text, "[")
       if idx == -1 {
           return nil, false
       }

       sub := text[idx:]
       lastComplete := strings.LastIndex(sub, "},")
       if lastComplete == -1 {
           lastComplete = strings.LastIndex(sub, "}")
           if lastComplete == -1 {
               return nil, false
           }
           sub = sub[:lastComplete+1] + "]"
       } else {
           sub = sub[:lastComplete+1] + "]"
       }

       var facts []ExtractedFact
       if err := json.Unmarshal([]byte(sub), &facts); err != nil {
           return nil, false
       }
       if len(facts) == 0 {
           return nil, false
       }

       var valid []ExtractedFact
       for _, f := range facts {
           if f.Content != "" {
               valid = append(valid, f)
           }
       }
       if len(valid) == 0 {
           return nil, false
       }
       return valid, true
   }

Optional improvement: add session/runId to the debug log for easier tracing:

   logger.Debug("importance: could not parse facts from response",
       "session", sessionKey,   // add
       "runId", runID,          // add
       "raw", truncate(text, 200))
